	   <tr><td colspan=2>Rarity doesn't apply here. The Spiderfur is almost universally better (would say this is better for warriors who solo and use the trick with taking off HP gear to bind wounds higher). No one is going to pay more for an inferior item. The only place rarity really affects prices is on lore items. So the light burlap sack costs more than the evil eye bag, even though the evil eye bag is superior, because people want both.<br><br>Of course, rarity can explain why item X, which is only slightly better than item Y, is ten times the value, or why some item that's real special purpose can be really expensive.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
